WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:17.770 align:middle line:90%


00:00:17.770 --> 00:00:20.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr,
host of Gaiam Inspirations.

00:00:20.690 --> 00:00:23.130 align:middle line:84%
Welcome to our Los
Angeles studio.

00:00:23.130 --> 00:00:27.110 align:middle line:84%
The 1998 Oscar award-winning
film "What Dreams May Come,"

00:00:27.110 --> 00:00:29.110 align:middle line:84%
starring Robin Williams
and Cuba Gooding,

00:00:29.110 --> 00:00:31.640 align:middle line:84%
Jr. was a movie that
was so far ahead

00:00:31.640 --> 00:00:34.110 align:middle line:84%
of its time in vision
and creativity.

00:00:34.110 --> 00:00:38.050 align:middle line:84%
And so is the film's
producer, Barnet Bain,

00:00:38.050 --> 00:00:39.240 align:middle line:90%
who is joining us today.

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:41.830 align:middle line:84%
Barnet is a creative
visionary and

00:00:41.830 --> 00:00:43.970 align:middle line:90%
a transformational producer.

00:00:43.970 --> 00:00:46.750 align:middle line:84%
He speaks all around the world
to corporations and individuals

00:00:46.750 --> 00:00:49.530 align:middle line:84%
about creativity
and spirituality.

00:00:49.530 --> 00:00:53.010 align:middle line:84%
And he has blessed us
today with his presence.

00:00:53.010 --> 00:00:55.539 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much for
being here, Barnet Bain.

00:00:55.539 --> 00:00:56.580 align:middle line:90%
>>BARNET BAIN: Thank you.

00:00:56.580 --> 00:00:59.540 align:middle line:84%
I am so glad to
be here with you.

00:00:59.540 --> 00:01:01.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Honestly,
the honor is mine.

00:01:01.040 --> 00:01:03.650 align:middle line:84%
You have such an
incredible visionary eye.

00:01:03.650 --> 00:01:05.950 align:middle line:84%
And I know you as
a friend, as well.

00:01:05.950 --> 00:01:08.790 align:middle line:84%
Once I saw you at
just a conference.

00:01:08.790 --> 00:01:10.690 align:middle line:84%
And you were looking
behind the video camera.

00:01:10.690 --> 00:01:12.440 align:middle line:84%
You just got up out of you
seat, an you just looked

00:01:12.440 --> 00:01:13.439 align:middle line:90%
behind the video camera.

00:01:13.439 --> 00:01:18.210 align:middle line:84%
And I was looking
at lifetimes of you

00:01:18.210 --> 00:01:20.230 align:middle line:84%
with the glasses
looking behind the lens.

00:01:20.230 --> 00:01:25.792 align:middle line:84%
You have a true talent and a
knack for visual production.

00:01:25.792 --> 00:01:27.500 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Well, fortunately
that conference

00:01:27.500 --> 00:01:29.060 align:middle line:84%
that you're talking
about we were

00:01:29.060 --> 00:01:31.180 align:middle line:84%
amongst our very
dearest friends.

00:01:31.180 --> 00:01:33.845 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, that might have been
considered annoying, I think.

00:01:33.845 --> 00:01:35.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You had
freedom to be yourself.

00:01:35.470 --> 00:01:36.040 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: Yeah.

00:01:36.040 --> 00:01:39.256 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, so now tell me
about where did you grow up?

00:01:39.256 --> 00:01:43.400 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: I was raised in a small
French Canadian town 70 miles

00:01:43.400 --> 00:01:45.650 align:middle line:84%
north of Montreal in
Sainte-Agathe-des-Monts,

00:01:45.650 --> 00:01:47.120 align:middle line:90%
Quebec.

00:01:47.120 --> 00:01:52.866 align:middle line:84%
My father was the local butcher,
and my mom was a housewife.

00:01:52.866 --> 00:01:54.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Were you really
highly creative as a child?

00:01:54.990 --> 00:01:57.742 align:middle line:90%


00:01:57.742 --> 00:02:00.720 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: I think we're all
highly creative as children.

00:02:00.720 --> 00:02:04.170 align:middle line:90%


00:02:04.170 --> 00:02:07.050 align:middle line:90%
It gets shoehorned out of us.

00:02:07.050 --> 00:02:12.060 align:middle line:84%
I have an image of this
huge, huge creative potential

00:02:12.060 --> 00:02:15.070 align:middle line:84%
that we all have, that
we all come in with.

00:02:15.070 --> 00:02:18.920 align:middle line:84%
And then it's like
we're shoehorned

00:02:18.920 --> 00:02:23.650 align:middle line:84%
into a very, very
tight fit with life.

00:02:23.650 --> 00:02:29.170 align:middle line:84%
We lose it as a result of
other people's thoughts,

00:02:29.170 --> 00:02:32.470 align:middle line:84%
and other people's
entertainment, and religions,

00:02:32.470 --> 00:02:37.310 align:middle line:84%
and television shows, and songs,
and education, and values,

00:02:37.310 --> 00:02:38.910 align:middle line:90%
and world view.

00:02:38.910 --> 00:02:43.590 align:middle line:84%
And pretty soon
there's not a lot

00:02:43.590 --> 00:02:46.780 align:middle line:84%
of welcoming for what we're
bringing to the table.

00:02:46.780 --> 00:02:48.500 align:middle line:84%
We're trying so
desperately to fit in

00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:52.410 align:middle line:84%
and to behave nicely
that our freedoms

00:02:52.410 --> 00:02:55.510 align:middle line:84%
to create and to express
get reduced, and reduced,

00:02:55.510 --> 00:02:56.010 align:middle line:90%
and reduced.

00:02:56.010 --> 00:02:58.230 align:middle line:84%
I call it a structured
imagination.

00:02:58.230 --> 00:03:01.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did that ever happen to
you, that structure happened--

00:03:01.090 --> 00:03:01.420 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: It sure did.

00:03:01.420 --> 00:03:01.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It did?

00:03:01.850 --> 00:03:02.683 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: It sure did.

00:03:02.683 --> 00:03:03.617 align:middle line:90%
It sure did.

00:03:03.617 --> 00:03:05.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you
didn't get conditioned

00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:07.040 align:middle line:90%
by-- well, that's a great point.

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:09.685 align:middle line:84%
I mean, all of those
social media outlets

00:03:09.685 --> 00:03:12.050 align:middle line:84%
and everything else that we
have around us provides us

00:03:12.050 --> 00:03:14.890 align:middle line:84%
with the visual
pictures that we are not

00:03:14.890 --> 00:03:17.320 align:middle line:84%
creating our own back to the
days where there was no TV.

00:03:17.320 --> 00:03:20.140 align:middle line:84%
And you get to create
your imagination.

00:03:20.140 --> 00:03:21.710 align:middle line:84%
Your imagination
creates pictures

00:03:21.710 --> 00:03:23.820 align:middle line:90%
that are not even in books.

00:03:23.820 --> 00:03:27.040 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: We get structured
more now than ever before,

00:03:27.040 --> 00:03:30.580 align:middle line:84%
but there's a flip
side to it, as well.

00:03:30.580 --> 00:03:33.710 align:middle line:84%
There's gold as a treasure
inside of that, as well,

00:03:33.710 --> 00:03:39.660 align:middle line:84%
because just as our imaginations
are structured by exposure

00:03:39.660 --> 00:03:45.550 align:middle line:84%
to so much input, similarly
on the way out when we realize

00:03:45.550 --> 00:03:51.080 align:middle line:84%
that, we have developed such
a capacity to create imagery

00:03:51.080 --> 00:03:54.690 align:middle line:84%
and to have an
understanding of psychology.

00:03:54.690 --> 00:03:58.010 align:middle line:84%
And we have such a
fertile experience

00:03:58.010 --> 00:04:02.420 align:middle line:84%
to draw from that when
we do get the picture,

00:04:02.420 --> 00:04:06.040 align:middle line:84%
and we can light the fuse to
escape that structured reality,

00:04:06.040 --> 00:04:07.380 align:middle line:90%
we really blast off.

00:04:07.380 --> 00:04:10.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, that's kind of
what you have done in a sense

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:12.490 align:middle line:84%
because you have, in
the past, expressed

00:04:12.490 --> 00:04:16.390 align:middle line:84%
your creativity through
film producing, television

00:04:16.390 --> 00:04:17.660 align:middle line:90%
producing.

00:04:17.660 --> 00:04:20.117 align:middle line:90%
How do you choose your projects?

00:04:20.117 --> 00:04:21.200 align:middle line:90%
Well, let me just back up?

00:04:21.200 --> 00:04:25.180 align:middle line:84%
How did you get into that
from the butcher's son

00:04:25.180 --> 00:04:29.520 align:middle line:84%
to coming to Hollywood and
becoming a film producer?

00:04:29.520 --> 00:04:30.970 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: Well, there's two parts.

00:04:30.970 --> 00:04:32.678 align:middle line:84%
There's two ways to
answer that question.

00:04:32.678 --> 00:04:37.870 align:middle line:90%
And the first is I had dreams.

00:04:37.870 --> 00:04:44.680 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that desire,
and dreaming, and expectation,

00:04:44.680 --> 00:04:52.370 align:middle line:84%
imagining, those are the
big raw materials out

00:04:52.370 --> 00:04:53.520 align:middle line:90%
of which we create lives.

00:04:53.520 --> 00:04:57.970 align:middle line:84%
And so I had not been
shoehorned into that structure

00:04:57.970 --> 00:05:00.280 align:middle line:84%
sufficiently where I
abandoned all dreams.

00:05:00.280 --> 00:05:02.020 align:middle line:90%
I still had dreams.

00:05:02.020 --> 00:05:06.470 align:middle line:84%
And I went off to college
after high school.

00:05:06.470 --> 00:05:09.330 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't do well.

00:05:09.330 --> 00:05:12.430 align:middle line:84%
I went from a town
of 3,000 people

00:05:12.430 --> 00:05:15.320 align:middle line:84%
to a somewhat bigger
town in Ottawa, Canada.

00:05:15.320 --> 00:05:19.850 align:middle line:84%
And I went wild, and
played, and partied.

00:05:19.850 --> 00:05:22.940 align:middle line:84%
And I flunked out of my first
year of college two years

00:05:22.940 --> 00:05:23.690 align:middle line:90%
in a row.

00:05:23.690 --> 00:05:24.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:05:24.860 --> 00:05:28.970 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: And went off to
Europe, and something

00:05:28.970 --> 00:05:34.950 align:middle line:84%
in the escape from the
community of my upbringing

00:05:34.950 --> 00:05:39.020 align:middle line:84%
allowed me to make different
kinds of choices, choices

00:05:39.020 --> 00:05:42.260 align:middle line:84%
that maybe I wouldn't have
felt as comfortable making

00:05:42.260 --> 00:05:44.010 align:middle line:90%
in my own community.

00:05:44.010 --> 00:05:49.940 align:middle line:84%
So I began to think of art,
and filmmaking, and photography

00:05:49.940 --> 00:05:53.250 align:middle line:84%
as a credible
career choice, which

00:05:53.250 --> 00:05:57.560 align:middle line:84%
would have been so far a
field in the community that I

00:05:57.560 --> 00:05:59.030 align:middle line:90%
was raised in.

00:05:59.030 --> 00:06:05.800 align:middle line:84%
So the chance crossing of
those two things-- well,

00:06:05.800 --> 00:06:08.530 align:middle line:84%
I have a friend that
used to say that life

00:06:08.530 --> 00:06:10.600 align:middle line:84%
is what happens when
you're making other plans.

00:06:10.600 --> 00:06:10.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:06:10.950 --> 00:06:11.450 align:middle line:90%
Uh-huh.

00:06:11.450 --> 00:06:13.616 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: And so I
thought I was going

00:06:13.616 --> 00:06:16.440 align:middle line:84%
to go in a particular
direction, and the direction

00:06:16.440 --> 00:06:21.590 align:middle line:84%
that I was socialized to go,
not quite in the butcher shop,

00:06:21.590 --> 00:06:26.750 align:middle line:84%
but a more conventional
profession.

00:06:26.750 --> 00:06:28.546 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Filmmaking
is a conventional--

00:06:28.546 --> 00:06:30.810 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: And instead, I
went into filmmaking,

00:06:30.810 --> 00:06:33.850 align:middle line:84%
which was such an
unconventional profession.

00:06:33.850 --> 00:06:37.200 align:middle line:84%
So these things kind of, they
just sort of happen, life

00:06:37.200 --> 00:06:40.110 align:middle line:90%
happens, and you just dream.

00:06:40.110 --> 00:06:42.410 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, you did
follow your dreams a lot.

00:06:42.410 --> 00:06:44.309 align:middle line:84%
What was the dream
that you were having?

00:06:44.309 --> 00:06:46.350 align:middle line:84%
I mean, specifically, was
there a specific dream,

00:06:46.350 --> 00:06:48.342 align:middle line:90%
or was it a series of--

00:06:48.342 --> 00:06:49.550 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: I dreamed of freedom.

00:06:49.550 --> 00:06:52.630 align:middle line:90%


00:06:52.630 --> 00:06:54.180 align:middle line:90%
I didn't hold it that way.

00:06:54.180 --> 00:06:58.580 align:middle line:84%
I didn't really understand it in
that way, but when I look back

00:06:58.580 --> 00:07:01.850 align:middle line:84%
and when in meditation, for
instance, when I spend time

00:07:01.850 --> 00:07:06.910 align:middle line:84%
with myself at earlier times
in my life, which I do daily

00:07:06.910 --> 00:07:11.750 align:middle line:84%
sometimes more than
once, I am very

00:07:11.750 --> 00:07:15.120 align:middle line:84%
intimate with those
past versions of myself.

00:07:15.120 --> 00:07:20.360 align:middle line:84%
And he did not really have
the courage or the support

00:07:20.360 --> 00:07:25.580 align:middle line:84%
to have big dreams, but
longed for the freedom.

00:07:25.580 --> 00:07:29.590 align:middle line:84%
Just didn't know how to
put his finger on why

00:07:29.590 --> 00:07:32.820 align:middle line:84%
life felt so tense,
why he felt such

00:07:32.820 --> 00:07:36.830 align:middle line:84%
a pressure to conform and to
be a part of the community

00:07:36.830 --> 00:07:40.550 align:middle line:84%
in the very rigid ways
the community held itself.

00:07:40.550 --> 00:07:45.020 align:middle line:84%
So I knew then that
that desire to be free

00:07:45.020 --> 00:07:47.490 align:middle line:84%
was a light that was
burning very, very bright.

00:07:47.490 --> 00:07:49.560 align:middle line:84%
And it happened to show
up in a lot of ways,

00:07:49.560 --> 00:07:52.975 align:middle line:84%
including well, I'll do what
would have been considered

00:07:52.975 --> 00:07:57.310 align:middle line:84%
a Bohemian life, and
I'll do photography,

00:07:57.310 --> 00:07:59.960 align:middle line:84%
and I'll start writing,
and I'll dabble in film.

00:07:59.960 --> 00:08:06.000 align:middle line:84%
And then eventually that
became a passionate interest

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:09.850 align:middle line:84%
in spirituality, and
consciousness, in metaphysics.

00:08:09.850 --> 00:08:12.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Not just anyone
makes it in the film industry

00:08:12.800 --> 00:08:14.800 align:middle line:84%
and then maintains
the integrity that you

00:08:14.800 --> 00:08:16.890 align:middle line:90%
have within the industry.

00:08:16.890 --> 00:08:20.050 align:middle line:84%
And it is your different
perspectives on life

00:08:20.050 --> 00:08:22.140 align:middle line:84%
that you bring to
your profession

00:08:22.140 --> 00:08:25.140 align:middle line:84%
that I think has allowed you to
have longevity that you've had

00:08:25.140 --> 00:08:30.710 align:middle line:84%
and also to continue on, even
with the different direction

00:08:30.710 --> 00:08:34.900 align:middle line:84%
with lecturing on creativity
and consciousness.

00:08:34.900 --> 00:08:39.795 align:middle line:84%
What enables you to hold on
to that aspect of your life

00:08:39.795 --> 00:08:48.246 align:middle line:84%
of semi-sanity, of creativity,
of consciousness in the world?

00:08:48.246 --> 00:08:49.220 align:middle line:90%
Small question.

00:08:49.220 --> 00:08:50.340 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Well, it's
a great question.

00:08:50.340 --> 00:08:51.256 align:middle line:90%
It's a great question.

00:08:51.256 --> 00:08:54.240 align:middle line:84%
And believe me, I ask
it of myself constantly.

00:08:54.240 --> 00:08:56.670 align:middle line:90%
I am in love.

00:08:56.670 --> 00:08:59.680 align:middle line:90%
I am in love with spirituality.

00:08:59.680 --> 00:09:04.255 align:middle line:84%
I am in love with discovering
more and more of who I am,

00:09:04.255 --> 00:09:09.320 align:middle line:84%
who I really am, and more
and more of who we all

00:09:09.320 --> 00:09:11.360 align:middle line:84%
are in relationship
to each other.

00:09:11.360 --> 00:09:17.170 align:middle line:84%
And I have always
felt the pull of that.

00:09:17.170 --> 00:09:19.610 align:middle line:84%
And more and more
pieces come together

00:09:19.610 --> 00:09:22.360 align:middle line:84%
like little pieces dropping
into a jigsaw puzzle.

00:09:22.360 --> 00:09:25.550 align:middle line:84%
Once upon a time,
the idea that we

00:09:25.550 --> 00:09:29.190 align:middle line:84%
are separate and yet
connected was an abstraction.

00:09:29.190 --> 00:09:31.820 align:middle line:84%
And now I feel it,
I experience it.

00:09:31.820 --> 00:09:33.980 align:middle line:90%
So I'm in love with it.

00:09:33.980 --> 00:09:39.610 align:middle line:90%
And it's so generous with me.

00:09:39.610 --> 00:09:43.140 align:middle line:84%
Even when it's difficult, I
always just get enough love--

00:09:43.140 --> 00:09:44.276 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah, wonderful.

00:09:44.276 --> 00:09:45.650 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: --to keep
me on the hunt.

00:09:45.650 --> 00:09:47.370 align:middle line:90%
I call it the big hunt.

00:09:47.370 --> 00:09:49.790 align:middle line:84%
And so there's nothing
really I can do.

00:09:49.790 --> 00:09:53.280 align:middle line:84%
And there was a
time in my past when

00:09:53.280 --> 00:09:58.560 align:middle line:84%
I would have been
seduced off of it.

00:09:58.560 --> 00:10:00.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Many do get seduced.

00:10:00.770 --> 00:10:04.170 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: A huge hit, a
huge business success,

00:10:04.170 --> 00:10:08.280 align:middle line:84%
a huge film hit-- that kind
of thing when I look back

00:10:08.280 --> 00:10:11.900 align:middle line:84%
may well have
seduced me off of it.

00:10:11.900 --> 00:10:14.390 align:middle line:84%
And so there were
sort of protections

00:10:14.390 --> 00:10:18.270 align:middle line:84%
that I built into the place
because it's so clear to me

00:10:18.270 --> 00:10:20.910 align:middle line:84%
that the choice that I
made in this lifetime

00:10:20.910 --> 00:10:28.230 align:middle line:84%
was to come home to the
love and to find and explore

00:10:28.230 --> 00:10:29.507 align:middle line:90%
what really matters.

00:10:29.507 --> 00:10:31.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Are you talking
about that hit being

00:10:31.340 --> 00:10:32.350 align:middle line:90%
"What Dreams May Come?"

00:10:32.350 --> 00:10:35.950 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: No, I'm talking about
anything that would have been

00:10:35.950 --> 00:10:37.660 align:middle line:90%
such an enormous--

00:10:37.660 --> 00:10:39.105 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:10:39.105 --> 00:10:41.480 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: --have such an enormous
impact that it might have

00:10:41.480 --> 00:10:47.110 align:middle line:84%
changed my life so dramatically
in terms of how the world

00:10:47.110 --> 00:10:49.730 align:middle line:90%
measures success--

00:10:49.730 --> 00:10:50.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:10:50.270 --> 00:10:54.320 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: --that it
might have moved me off

00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:57.380 align:middle line:90%
of the trail of my life.

00:10:57.380 --> 00:10:59.440 align:middle line:90%
So those were the earlier years.

00:10:59.440 --> 00:11:02.594 align:middle line:84%
And now, as you were saying,
what keeps you at this?

00:11:02.594 --> 00:11:03.177 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:11:03.177 --> 00:11:07.160 align:middle line:90%


00:11:07.160 --> 00:11:09.070 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Never say
never, but there

00:11:09.070 --> 00:11:14.790 align:middle line:84%
is no seduction that is
going to turn me away

00:11:14.790 --> 00:11:18.680 align:middle line:84%
from a path that has been
so beautiful, and magical,

00:11:18.680 --> 00:11:20.090 align:middle line:90%
and generous.

00:11:20.090 --> 00:11:21.450 align:middle line:90%
So I've matured into it.

00:11:21.450 --> 00:11:24.884 align:middle line:84%
And that's the best answer that
I can come to, and I just--

00:11:24.884 --> 00:11:25.384 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:11:25.384 --> 00:11:26.060 align:middle line:90%
It's a beautiful answer.

00:11:26.060 --> 00:11:27.143 align:middle line:90%
That's a beautiful answer.

00:11:27.143 --> 00:11:30.220 align:middle line:84%
Did you go through periods
of studying meditation

00:11:30.220 --> 00:11:33.940 align:middle line:84%
or of long journeys
within a certain type

00:11:33.940 --> 00:11:39.880 align:middle line:84%
of a teacher or a journey in
your life prior to filmmaking?

00:11:39.880 --> 00:11:43.210 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Prior to
filmmaking, absolutely.

00:11:43.210 --> 00:11:46.410 align:middle line:84%
When I was very little,
I lived in this town

00:11:46.410 --> 00:11:49.720 align:middle line:84%
that we talked about of 3,000
people, French Canadian town.

00:11:49.720 --> 00:11:53.360 align:middle line:84%
And it was a tourist
town, so in the winter

00:11:53.360 --> 00:11:56.570 align:middle line:84%
there was nobody in the
town except on weekends

00:11:56.570 --> 00:11:57.680 align:middle line:90%
because it was a ski town.

00:11:57.680 --> 00:12:01.830 align:middle line:84%
So we'd go from 3,000 to
like 6,000 on the weekends

00:12:01.830 --> 00:12:03.270 align:middle line:90%
when the snow was on the ground.

00:12:03.270 --> 00:12:06.700 align:middle line:84%
And in the summer, it would
go to 40,000 or 50,000.

00:12:06.700 --> 00:12:11.600 align:middle line:84%
There were people that had
little summer cottages.

00:12:11.600 --> 00:12:14.970 align:middle line:84%
It was a small
French Canadian town.

00:12:14.970 --> 00:12:18.570 align:middle line:84%
My ethnicity and religious
background is Jewish.

00:12:18.570 --> 00:12:22.860 align:middle line:84%
And I lived in a town that
had like 10 Jewish families--

00:12:22.860 --> 00:12:24.900 align:middle line:90%
--but there was a synagogue.

00:12:24.900 --> 00:12:27.800 align:middle line:84%
And the synagogue was there
because in the summer time

00:12:27.800 --> 00:12:30.490 align:middle line:84%
there were all these
people to fill it.

00:12:30.490 --> 00:12:34.900 align:middle line:84%
And so, at one point when
I was very young, even then

00:12:34.900 --> 00:12:40.410 align:middle line:84%
I latched on to
the call of spirit.

00:12:40.410 --> 00:12:44.014 align:middle line:84%
And I thought then that I
was going to be a rabbi.

00:12:44.014 --> 00:12:44.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:12:44.870 --> 00:12:47.085 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: So, yes, this
is a very, very long--

00:12:47.085 --> 00:12:47.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Long journey for you.

00:12:47.680 --> 00:12:48.638 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: --long journey.

00:12:48.638 --> 00:12:52.430 align:middle line:84%
And the first film that I
was ever involved in was-- I

00:12:52.430 --> 00:12:56.490 align:middle line:84%
wrote "The Jesus Film,"
which if you Google it,

00:12:56.490 --> 00:12:59.420 align:middle line:84%
it's the most widely
seen film on the planet.

00:12:59.420 --> 00:13:04.920 align:middle line:84%
And so even when I didn't
know I was wandering,

00:13:04.920 --> 00:13:09.140 align:middle line:84%
I have never wandered too
far off the soft shoulder

00:13:09.140 --> 00:13:12.777 align:middle line:90%
on either side of the road.

00:13:12.777 --> 00:13:14.360 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So when the
script came to you

00:13:14.360 --> 00:13:17.610 align:middle line:84%
of "What Dreams may
Come," did you immediately

00:13:17.610 --> 00:13:19.650 align:middle line:84%
resonate with that
film as being something

00:13:19.650 --> 00:13:25.140 align:middle line:84%
that you thought was going to
express your inner feeling?

00:13:25.140 --> 00:13:27.070 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: At the time
that that script came,

00:13:27.070 --> 00:13:30.490 align:middle line:84%
I was partnered with a
gentleman named Stephen Simon.

00:13:30.490 --> 00:13:33.310 align:middle line:84%
And Stephen had
developed that script.

00:13:33.310 --> 00:13:35.710 align:middle line:84%
He had developed it
for many, many years.

00:13:35.710 --> 00:13:39.350 align:middle line:84%
And we partnered up,
and the first time

00:13:39.350 --> 00:13:41.546 align:middle line:90%
that I saw that movie, I cried.

00:13:41.546 --> 00:13:43.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:13:43.470 --> 00:13:44.780 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: I still get choked up.

00:13:44.780 --> 00:13:52.560 align:middle line:84%
I cried because I thought
oh my goodness, this

00:13:52.560 --> 00:13:57.500 align:middle line:84%
has given expression to a more
of what matters to me that I

00:13:57.500 --> 00:14:00.630 align:middle line:84%
hold as beautiful, and
good, and true than anything

00:14:00.630 --> 00:14:05.047 align:middle line:90%
that I have experienced in film.

00:14:05.047 --> 00:14:06.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Just when
you read the script?

00:14:06.630 --> 00:14:07.410 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Just when
I read the script.

00:14:07.410 --> 00:14:09.243 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it popped
off the page instantly.

00:14:09.243 --> 00:14:12.810 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: And so I
thought what a miracle.

00:14:12.810 --> 00:14:16.350 align:middle line:84%
And that was a gift
from Stephen to me.

00:14:16.350 --> 00:14:17.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wonderful.

00:14:17.190 --> 00:14:18.510 align:middle line:84%
Well, let's take a
look at this actually.

00:14:18.510 --> 00:14:20.801 align:middle line:84%
There's a couple of clips
that we have around the movie

00:14:20.801 --> 00:14:23.540 align:middle line:84%
that you have found
some beautiful teaching

00:14:23.540 --> 00:14:24.410 align:middle line:90%
moments within.

00:14:24.410 --> 00:14:26.490 align:middle line:84%
And it's really one
of my favorite movies.

00:14:26.490 --> 00:14:28.970 align:middle line:84%
And this is one of my favorite
scenes from the movie.

00:14:28.970 --> 00:14:30.986 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look.

00:14:30.986 --> 00:14:32.360 align:middle line:84%
>>CHRIS: Nice
place you got here.

00:14:32.360 --> 00:14:33.568 align:middle line:90%
>>ALBERT: Oh, no, no, no, no.

00:14:33.568 --> 00:14:35.820 align:middle line:90%
Nice place you got here.

00:14:35.820 --> 00:14:36.580 align:middle line:90%
>>CHRIS: Me?

00:14:36.580 --> 00:14:37.310 align:middle line:90%
>>ALBERT: Sure!

00:14:37.310 --> 00:14:39.440 align:middle line:90%
You're making all of this.

00:14:39.440 --> 00:14:41.250 align:middle line:84%
See, we're all pretty
insecure at first,

00:14:41.250 --> 00:14:44.052 align:middle line:84%
so we see ourself
somewhere safe, comforting.

00:14:44.052 --> 00:14:45.760 align:middle line:84%
We all paint our own
surroundings, Chris,

00:14:45.760 --> 00:14:49.064 align:middle line:84%
but you're the first guy
I know to use real paint.

00:14:49.064 --> 00:14:50.480 align:middle line:84%
>>CHRIS: There is
so much here she

00:14:50.480 --> 00:14:56.850 align:middle line:90%
didn't paint, like that bird.

00:14:56.850 --> 00:14:58.370 align:middle line:84%
>>ALBERT: And it
gave you a start,

00:14:58.370 --> 00:15:00.010 align:middle line:84%
sort of like holding
on to hand rails.

00:15:00.010 --> 00:15:02.400 align:middle line:84%
Now you're creating
an entire world here

00:15:02.400 --> 00:15:04.530 align:middle line:84%
from your imagination,
from paintings

00:15:04.530 --> 00:15:07.110 align:middle line:90%
you love, anything you want.

00:15:07.110 --> 00:15:08.742 align:middle line:90%
>>CHRIS: Why doesn't it move?

00:15:08.742 --> 00:15:10.450 align:middle line:84%
>>ALBERT: It'll move
when you want it to.

00:15:10.450 --> 00:15:18.130 align:middle line:90%


00:15:18.130 --> 00:15:19.570 align:middle line:90%
>>ALBERT: Ho hoo!

00:15:19.570 --> 00:15:20.274 align:middle line:90%
You go boy!

00:15:20.274 --> 00:15:21.440 align:middle line:90%
>>CHRIS: Can I make it dive?

00:15:21.440 --> 00:15:22.925 align:middle line:84%
>>ALBERT: You're
the painter now.

00:15:22.925 --> 00:15:24.410 align:middle line:90%
It's your world!

00:15:24.410 --> 00:15:27.208 align:middle line:90%
>>CHRIS: Yeaaaaah aha!

00:15:27.208 --> 00:15:27.833 align:middle line:90%
>>ALBERT: Whoo!

00:15:27.833 --> 00:15:29.312 align:middle line:90%
Hahahaha.

00:15:29.312 --> 00:15:30.298 align:middle line:90%
Look at it go.

00:15:30.298 --> 00:15:32.270 align:middle line:90%
Whoo!

00:15:32.270 --> 00:15:33.982 align:middle line:84%
>>CHRIS: How about
maybe turquoise wings?

00:15:33.982 --> 00:15:35.866 align:middle line:84%
>>ALBERT: Turquoise
in the house!

00:15:35.866 --> 00:15:38.230 align:middle line:84%
>>CHRIS: And a little
mauve, all right.

00:15:38.230 --> 00:15:40.515 align:middle line:90%
>>ALBERT: Whoo hoo hoo!

00:15:40.515 --> 00:15:41.098 align:middle line:90%
>>CHRIS: Whoa!

00:15:41.098 --> 00:15:48.160 align:middle line:90%


00:15:48.160 --> 00:15:48.970 align:middle line:90%
[SPLAT]

00:15:48.970 --> 00:15:55.200 align:middle line:90%


00:15:55.200 --> 00:15:56.677 align:middle line:90%
>>CHRIS: I didn't do that.

00:15:56.677 --> 00:15:57.510 align:middle line:90%
>>ALBERT: No, I did.

00:15:57.510 --> 00:16:00.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This movie is
so important in my life,

00:16:00.550 --> 00:16:04.140 align:middle line:84%
but that was a
wonderful, incredible way

00:16:04.140 --> 00:16:06.810 align:middle line:84%
of showing what
we-- that we create

00:16:06.810 --> 00:16:09.190 align:middle line:84%
our own realities in
certain ways, right?

00:16:09.190 --> 00:16:12.440 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Yeah, to me,
it's a documentary.

00:16:12.440 --> 00:16:14.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A documentary?

00:16:14.160 --> 00:16:18.850 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Cuba says, "We all
create our own reality.

00:16:18.850 --> 00:16:22.690 align:middle line:84%
You're just the first
one to use real paint."

00:16:22.690 --> 00:16:27.770 align:middle line:84%
In this clip, he's
creating in a dream.

00:16:27.770 --> 00:16:29.440 align:middle line:84%
And in this particular
dream, it happens

00:16:29.440 --> 00:16:30.570 align:middle line:90%
to be an afterlife dream.

00:16:30.570 --> 00:16:32.440 align:middle line:90%
He's passed on.

00:16:32.440 --> 00:16:36.750 align:middle line:84%
But who's to say
that that is not

00:16:36.750 --> 00:16:38.750 align:middle line:90%
how we generate all of this.

00:16:38.750 --> 00:16:41.800 align:middle line:84%
I certainly have an
inkling that it is.

00:16:41.800 --> 00:16:42.890 align:middle line:90%
I'm not-- I'm just saying.

00:16:42.890 --> 00:16:43.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No.

00:16:43.390 --> 00:16:44.070 align:middle line:90%
We know.

00:16:44.070 --> 00:16:46.984 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it makes
sense in every level.

00:16:46.984 --> 00:16:48.150 align:middle line:90%
Scientific level, whatever--

00:16:48.150 --> 00:16:49.270 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: At every level.

00:16:49.270 --> 00:16:52.360 align:middle line:84%
And there are ways
that we do it.

00:16:52.360 --> 00:16:57.490 align:middle line:84%
So, as we said before,
there are raw materials

00:16:57.490 --> 00:17:01.810 align:middle line:84%
which are desire, and
expectation, and imagination.

00:17:01.810 --> 00:17:05.079 align:middle line:84%
And we work on those raw
materials in the same way

00:17:05.079 --> 00:17:08.650 align:middle line:84%
that a painter uses
colors or a sculptor

00:17:08.650 --> 00:17:10.680 align:middle line:90%
uses a chisel on marble.

00:17:10.680 --> 00:17:14.460 align:middle line:84%
We chisel away at those raw
materials with some tools.

00:17:14.460 --> 00:17:18.310 align:middle line:84%
And those tools are our
beliefs, and our thoughts,

00:17:18.310 --> 00:17:20.190 align:middle line:84%
and our choices,
and our decisions,

00:17:20.190 --> 00:17:22.750 align:middle line:84%
and our attitudes,
and our feelings.

00:17:22.750 --> 00:17:30.283 align:middle line:84%
And the interplay between
those shows up on the,

00:17:30.283 --> 00:17:33.050 align:middle line:90%
I call it the holodeck.

00:17:33.050 --> 00:17:34.227 align:middle line:90%
It's like the--

00:17:34.227 --> 00:17:34.935 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Holodeck.

00:17:34.935 --> 00:17:35.893 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: --the holodeck.

00:17:35.893 --> 00:17:36.970 align:middle line:90%
We are walking--

00:17:36.970 --> 00:17:37.245 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --holographic--

00:17:37.245 --> 00:17:38.661 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: --the
holographic reality.

00:17:38.661 --> 00:17:43.580 align:middle line:84%
We're literally moving with
a deeper and deeper and more

00:17:43.580 --> 00:17:46.810 align:middle line:84%
and more intimate awareness
of that process is happening

00:17:46.810 --> 00:17:49.520 align:middle line:84%
all the time, certainly for
our listeners here today.

00:17:49.520 --> 00:17:52.680 align:middle line:84%
They are committed
to this exploration.

00:17:52.680 --> 00:17:54.700 align:middle line:84%
And so what is
happening here is we

00:17:54.700 --> 00:17:59.640 align:middle line:84%
are very consciously becoming
intimate with our subconscious.

00:17:59.640 --> 00:18:02.930 align:middle line:84%
We are walking through our
subconscious all the time.

00:18:02.930 --> 00:18:04.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, just
as he had painted

00:18:04.700 --> 00:18:08.540 align:middle line:84%
the bird a different
color, we do that when

00:18:08.540 --> 00:18:11.360 align:middle line:84%
we make a conscious
choice to take

00:18:11.360 --> 00:18:12.987 align:middle line:84%
a different direction
in our life.

00:18:12.987 --> 00:18:15.070 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: We do that when
we make a conscious choice

00:18:15.070 --> 00:18:16.390 align:middle line:90%
to take a different direction.

00:18:16.390 --> 00:18:21.330 align:middle line:84%
We do that when we
shift an emotional state

00:18:21.330 --> 00:18:24.720 align:middle line:84%
from feeling helpless,
or hopeless, or anxious,

00:18:24.720 --> 00:18:30.670 align:middle line:84%
or unappreciated,
or happy, glad, sad.

00:18:30.670 --> 00:18:35.280 align:middle line:84%
Every shift changes
the frequency game.

00:18:35.280 --> 00:18:39.160 align:middle line:84%
And no thought, or action,
or feeling, or belief

00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:39.980 align:middle line:90%
goes in ernest.

00:18:39.980 --> 00:18:43.420 align:middle line:84%
Every one of those
ripples across eternity.

00:18:43.420 --> 00:18:44.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And when
you made a choice

00:18:44.960 --> 00:18:48.240 align:middle line:84%
to start going into
corporations and lecturing

00:18:48.240 --> 00:18:50.332 align:middle line:84%
about consciousness,
how did that happen?

00:18:50.332 --> 00:18:52.040 align:middle line:84%
How did that paintbrush
direction happen?

00:18:52.040 --> 00:18:53.331 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: I was actually invited.

00:18:53.331 --> 00:18:53.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:18:53.870 --> 00:18:55.203 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: That's how it showed up.

00:18:55.203 --> 00:18:59.840 align:middle line:84%
I used to think that
seeing is believing,

00:18:59.840 --> 00:19:01.330 align:middle line:90%
and that cause leads to effect.

00:19:01.330 --> 00:19:03.050 align:middle line:90%
And I don't hold that anymore.

00:19:03.050 --> 00:19:08.750 align:middle line:84%
It's true, but there's a
overarching, a superseding way

00:19:08.750 --> 00:19:10.810 align:middle line:90%
that reality works, as well.

00:19:10.810 --> 00:19:13.750 align:middle line:84%
And that has to do with
well, effects lead to causes.

00:19:13.750 --> 00:19:19.860 align:middle line:84%
And because I had
a tremendous desire

00:19:19.860 --> 00:19:24.170 align:middle line:84%
to reach out to corporations
and to work not just

00:19:24.170 --> 00:19:26.370 align:middle line:84%
in the entertainment business
as much as I love it,

00:19:26.370 --> 00:19:30.690 align:middle line:84%
but with schools, and educators,
and with corporations,

00:19:30.690 --> 00:19:33.130 align:middle line:84%
because I had such
a desire for it,

00:19:33.130 --> 00:19:39.330 align:middle line:84%
at some point energy follows
attention, it manifested.

00:19:39.330 --> 00:19:44.050 align:middle line:84%
So effects lead to
causes in a more real way

00:19:44.050 --> 00:19:45.410 align:middle line:90%
than causes lead to effects.

00:19:45.410 --> 00:19:47.420 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:19:47.420 --> 00:19:48.990 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: I held that intention.

00:19:48.990 --> 00:19:52.060 align:middle line:84%
I often imagined
how that would work,

00:19:52.060 --> 00:19:53.540 align:middle line:90%
and I did it quite consciously.

00:19:53.540 --> 00:19:57.500 align:middle line:84%
And then one day someone who was
working for a big corporation--

00:19:57.500 --> 00:19:59.625 align:middle line:84%
they're actually the company
that is putting the XL

00:19:59.625 --> 00:20:06.230 align:middle line:84%
pipeline-- building the XL
pipeline-- somebody asked

00:20:06.230 --> 00:20:09.320 align:middle line:84%
if I would come
and work with them.

00:20:09.320 --> 00:20:10.380 align:middle line:90%
And I did.

00:20:10.380 --> 00:20:12.360 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Work with
them on creativity?

00:20:12.360 --> 00:20:14.900 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Work with them on
creativity, and innovation,

00:20:14.900 --> 00:20:21.650 align:middle line:84%
and aligning inside
their divisions,

00:20:21.650 --> 00:20:24.610 align:middle line:84%
aligning some of the
teams so that everybody

00:20:24.610 --> 00:20:25.780 align:middle line:90%
was holding the same story.

00:20:25.780 --> 00:20:29.330 align:middle line:84%
And they were really,
really wonderful.

00:20:29.330 --> 00:20:29.839 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:20:29.839 --> 00:20:30.880 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: Really wonderful.

00:20:30.880 --> 00:20:40.180 align:middle line:84%
So I operate from a passionate
relationship with creativity.

00:20:40.180 --> 00:20:44.150 align:middle line:84%
And I am convinced
that right now business

00:20:44.150 --> 00:20:48.900 align:middle line:84%
is the primary area of
creativity on the planet.

00:20:48.900 --> 00:20:52.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, in my opinion,
it needs the most creativity

00:20:52.870 --> 00:20:55.970 align:middle line:84%
at this point because we are
having to reinvent ourselves

00:20:55.970 --> 00:20:58.460 align:middle line:90%
in business across the board.

00:20:58.460 --> 00:21:01.686 align:middle line:84%
And even there is an
increase in entrepreneurs.

00:21:01.686 --> 00:21:03.310 align:middle line:84%
And entrepreneurs
are constantly having

00:21:03.310 --> 00:21:06.980 align:middle line:84%
to reinvent themselves, which
is another definite need

00:21:06.980 --> 00:21:08.250 align:middle line:90%
for creativity.

00:21:08.250 --> 00:21:10.330 align:middle line:90%
So how do you bridge that gap?

00:21:10.330 --> 00:21:12.365 align:middle line:84%
How do you take a
corporation or even

00:21:12.365 --> 00:21:17.220 align:middle line:84%
an individual out of the mold
that isn't working any longer?

00:21:17.220 --> 00:21:20.220 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Well, very
briefly, we refer

00:21:20.220 --> 00:21:25.490 align:middle line:84%
to how realities
are created, belief,

00:21:25.490 --> 00:21:28.420 align:middle line:84%
thought, choice, decision,
actions, and feelings,

00:21:28.420 --> 00:21:31.820 align:middle line:84%
and working upon imagination,
and expectations.

00:21:31.820 --> 00:21:36.450 align:middle line:84%
And that is also how
corporations operate.

00:21:36.450 --> 00:21:38.990 align:middle line:84%
They aren't as conscious
about it in that way.

00:21:38.990 --> 00:21:40.180 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes they are.

00:21:40.180 --> 00:21:43.337 align:middle line:84%
They don't hold it in the
language of metaphysics--

