to create safety for another, to
reduce the risk of abandonment,

00:31:29.670 --> 00:31:34.000 align:middle line:84%
or loneliness, or
fear, or humiliation.

00:31:34.000 --> 00:31:37.190 align:middle line:84%
If I can do that not as an
obligation, but as a gift.

00:31:37.190 --> 00:31:39.150 align:middle line:90%
If I can do that, that's loving.

00:31:39.150 --> 00:31:43.130 align:middle line:84%
If I can increase pleasure for
another person emotionally,

00:31:43.130 --> 00:31:46.075 align:middle line:84%
mentally, and physically when
appropriate, where appropriate,

00:31:46.075 --> 00:31:50.190 align:middle line:84%
and how appropriate,
all of these things

00:31:50.190 --> 00:31:54.940 align:middle line:84%
as in a live, and vital,
and growing relationship,

00:31:54.940 --> 00:31:57.070 align:middle line:84%
the boundaries of
those possibilities

00:31:57.070 --> 00:31:58.450 align:middle line:90%
are constantly growing.

00:31:58.450 --> 00:32:02.830 align:middle line:84%
So I'm always pregnant with
what is possible for tomorrow.

00:32:02.830 --> 00:32:03.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:32:03.520 --> 00:32:06.080 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: That keeps it
alive, it keeps it juicy,

00:32:06.080 --> 00:32:11.390 align:middle line:84%
and it keeps it humble
because we never

00:32:11.390 --> 00:32:13.269 align:middle line:84%
have the assumption
that I know what

00:32:13.269 --> 00:32:14.560 align:middle line:90%
it's going to be like tomorrow.

00:32:14.560 --> 00:32:16.635 align:middle line:84%
And in my relationship
with Sandy--

00:32:16.635 --> 00:32:18.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Sandy, your wife, yeah.

00:32:18.700 --> 00:32:20.310 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: --we go
through like phases

00:32:20.310 --> 00:32:23.660 align:middle line:84%
where one or the
other of us starts

00:32:23.660 --> 00:32:25.310 align:middle line:90%
to take the other for granted.

00:32:25.310 --> 00:32:27.730 align:middle line:84%
Or think, you know, I think
I know what she wants,

00:32:27.730 --> 00:32:31.030 align:middle line:90%
or I think I know, or--

00:32:31.030 --> 00:32:33.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's how we
lose our creativity, what

00:32:33.220 --> 00:32:33.880 align:middle line:90%
you're talking about now.

00:32:33.880 --> 00:32:35.546 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: That's what
loses the creativity

00:32:35.546 --> 00:32:36.610 align:middle line:90%
in that relationship.

00:32:36.610 --> 00:32:40.510 align:middle line:84%
And to pedal back for
a second, whether it's

00:32:40.510 --> 00:32:43.420 align:middle line:84%
a relationship with
a significant other,

00:32:43.420 --> 00:32:45.110 align:middle line:84%
or it's a relationship
with my work,

00:32:45.110 --> 00:32:48.990 align:middle line:84%
or it's a relationship with
a creative project, or a pet,

00:32:48.990 --> 00:32:49.760 align:middle line:90%
or my daughter--

00:32:49.760 --> 00:32:50.343 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:32:50.343 --> 00:32:53.600 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: --or it's a relationship
with my drive to work, or to

00:32:53.600 --> 00:32:57.680 align:middle line:84%
and from the studio,
the degree to which I'm

00:32:57.680 --> 00:33:02.150 align:middle line:84%
present in it makes
it alive and juicy.

00:33:02.150 --> 00:33:04.340 align:middle line:84%
The more that I
am either absent,

00:33:04.340 --> 00:33:08.160 align:middle line:84%
or in my head, or
ruminating about yesterday,

00:33:08.160 --> 00:33:11.900 align:middle line:84%
or obsessing about
tomorrow-- and I

00:33:11.900 --> 00:33:13.200 align:middle line:90%
understand the pressures of it.

00:33:13.200 --> 00:33:15.080 align:middle line:90%
I don't live in a cave.

00:33:15.080 --> 00:33:17.300 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But that's
how you create.

00:33:17.300 --> 00:33:18.680 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: That's how you create.

00:33:18.680 --> 00:33:21.227 align:middle line:84%
What you put your
attention on, you find.

00:33:21.227 --> 00:33:22.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's how
you create reality.

00:33:22.810 --> 00:33:23.790 align:middle line:90%
You are right.

00:33:23.790 --> 00:33:26.450 align:middle line:84%
Everything, you are in
relationship to everything.

00:33:26.450 --> 00:33:28.200 align:middle line:84%
If you're trying to
create the next thing,

00:33:28.200 --> 00:33:31.450 align:middle line:84%
you create it within the
relationship you have to it.

00:33:31.450 --> 00:33:32.580 align:middle line:90%
That is such a huge piece.

00:33:32.580 --> 00:33:33.663 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: That's everything.

00:33:33.663 --> 00:33:35.030 align:middle line:90%
We are two things.

00:33:35.030 --> 00:33:39.300 align:middle line:84%
We are creators, and
we are in relationship.

00:33:39.300 --> 00:33:40.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:33:40.430 --> 00:33:43.720 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: So if people
who are watching

00:33:43.720 --> 00:33:45.570 align:middle line:84%
come away with nothing
more than that,

00:33:45.570 --> 00:33:47.400 align:middle line:84%
it will have been
a glorious day.

00:33:47.400 --> 00:33:48.890 align:middle line:90%
We are creators.

00:33:48.890 --> 00:33:51.160 align:middle line:90%
Creativity is love's work.

00:33:51.160 --> 00:33:52.590 align:middle line:90%
We are creators.

00:33:52.590 --> 00:33:53.970 align:middle line:90%
And we are in relationship.

00:33:53.970 --> 00:33:57.960 align:middle line:90%


00:33:57.960 --> 00:34:00.030 align:middle line:90%
Some say that there is only one.

00:34:00.030 --> 00:34:02.790 align:middle line:84%
And that's true, but I am
not operating at the place

00:34:02.790 --> 00:34:05.680 align:middle line:84%
where I experience
myself as one.

00:34:05.680 --> 00:34:06.901 align:middle line:90%
I have moments, peak moments.

00:34:06.901 --> 00:34:07.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:34:07.400 --> 00:34:12.000 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: So right now part
of the game of my creativity

00:34:12.000 --> 00:34:15.760 align:middle line:84%
is that I am both
separate and one.

00:34:15.760 --> 00:34:19.070 align:middle line:84%
And I am in
relationship with all

00:34:19.070 --> 00:34:23.810 align:middle line:84%
of the diverse, myriad,
infinite experiences myself.

00:34:23.810 --> 00:34:26.381 align:middle line:90%
And we play the love game.

00:34:26.381 --> 00:34:27.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's a
great way to learn

00:34:27.880 --> 00:34:29.449 align:middle line:90%
that is by having a child.

00:34:29.449 --> 00:34:31.670 align:middle line:84%
In your relationship
to everything,

00:34:31.670 --> 00:34:33.090 align:middle line:90%
they will reflect and mirror.

00:34:33.090 --> 00:34:35.199 align:middle line:84%
Your relationship to how
you hold your coffee cup,

00:34:35.199 --> 00:34:36.407 align:middle line:90%
they will reflect and mirror.

00:34:36.407 --> 00:34:39.199 align:middle line:84%
Your relationship to who
you're talking to on the phone,

00:34:39.199 --> 00:34:41.830 align:middle line:90%
they will imitate.

00:34:41.830 --> 00:34:47.132 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: You model an appetite
for life, it gets passed on.

00:34:47.132 --> 00:34:48.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And you can see that.

00:34:48.340 --> 00:34:51.199 align:middle line:84%
It's a wonderful way-- I
mean, conscious parenting

00:34:51.199 --> 00:34:53.770 align:middle line:84%
is a wonderful system
for accountability.

00:34:53.770 --> 00:34:55.020 align:middle line:90%
You do this in your life.

00:34:55.020 --> 00:34:58.900 align:middle line:84%
I mean, by calling attention to
that everything is relationship

00:34:58.900 --> 00:35:02.290 align:middle line:90%
is a hugely vital lesson.

00:35:02.290 --> 00:35:06.170 align:middle line:84%
It's a very distinct lesson,
but it's a beautiful lesson

00:35:06.170 --> 00:35:06.950 align:middle line:90%
to learn.

00:35:06.950 --> 00:35:07.824 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely beautiful.

00:35:07.824 --> 00:35:10.150 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: It's creative
relationships.

00:35:10.150 --> 00:35:13.200 align:middle line:84%
There are so many
in our community,

00:35:13.200 --> 00:35:16.780 align:middle line:84%
many of our friends-- we move
in largely the same circles--

00:35:16.780 --> 00:35:22.880 align:middle line:84%
many of our friends are some
of the leaders of conversations

00:35:22.880 --> 00:35:25.750 align:middle line:84%
like law of attraction, which
are beautiful and powerful,

00:35:25.750 --> 00:35:28.794 align:middle line:90%
powerful focuses.

00:35:28.794 --> 00:35:29.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Relationships.

00:35:29.710 --> 00:35:30.710 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: --Relationships.

00:35:30.710 --> 00:35:34.960 align:middle line:84%
And law of attraction
is a great example,

00:35:34.960 --> 00:35:39.040 align:middle line:84%
because what is
law of attraction?

00:35:39.040 --> 00:35:45.080 align:middle line:84%
What draws us to want to have
an understanding and an ease

00:35:45.080 --> 00:35:47.090 align:middle line:90%
with law of attraction?

00:35:47.090 --> 00:35:51.130 align:middle line:84%
What is it except
the desire to create?

00:35:51.130 --> 00:35:52.070 align:middle line:90%
To create what?

00:35:52.070 --> 00:35:56.190 align:middle line:84%
To create more bounty, more
prosperity, more abundance,

00:35:56.190 --> 00:36:00.680 align:middle line:84%
more flow, more intimacy, more
connection, more whatever the

00:36:00.680 --> 00:36:05.470 align:middle line:90%
what is, the verb is to create.

00:36:05.470 --> 00:36:09.670 align:middle line:84%
It is more properly
the laws of creation.

00:36:09.670 --> 00:36:12.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that in that
way, we can use our mind

00:36:12.790 --> 00:36:17.420 align:middle line:84%
to create whatever is
true in our reality.

00:36:17.420 --> 00:36:17.972 align:middle line:90%
Another--

00:36:17.972 --> 00:36:18.930 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: And our hearts.

00:36:18.930 --> 00:36:21.020 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --another great point
from the movie "What Dreams

00:36:21.020 --> 00:36:21.520 align:middle line:90%
May Come."

00:36:21.520 --> 00:36:23.740 align:middle line:84%
That's why I say this was
so far ahead of its time.

00:36:23.740 --> 00:36:26.270 align:middle line:84%
And this whole
movie is basically

00:36:26.270 --> 00:36:28.900 align:middle line:84%
the law of attraction,
and it's couched

00:36:28.900 --> 00:36:31.400 align:middle line:90%
around death and suicide.

00:36:31.400 --> 00:36:32.550 align:middle line:90%
It's phenomenal.

00:36:32.550 --> 00:36:36.880 align:middle line:84%
Take a look at this clip
about whatever is in our minds

00:36:36.880 --> 00:36:39.650 align:middle line:90%
is true.

00:36:39.650 --> 00:36:41.520 align:middle line:90%
[VERY SOFT SINGING]

00:36:41.520 --> 00:36:45.710 align:middle line:84%
>>CHRIS: I need to talk to you,
and you don't have to respond.

00:36:45.710 --> 00:36:54.080 align:middle line:90%


00:36:54.080 --> 00:36:57.485 align:middle line:90%
This is a one-way ticket for me.

00:36:57.485 --> 00:37:00.330 align:middle line:90%


00:37:00.330 --> 00:37:03.345 align:middle line:84%
My hanging around here
is not helping you,

00:37:03.345 --> 00:37:05.880 align:middle line:90%
and it's killing me.

00:37:05.880 --> 00:37:10.300 align:middle line:90%
So today is kind of a D Day.

00:37:10.300 --> 00:37:12.490 align:middle line:90%
D for decision, I guess.

00:37:12.490 --> 00:37:16.466 align:middle line:90%


00:37:16.466 --> 00:37:19.327 align:middle line:90%
Well, divorce.

00:37:19.327 --> 00:37:21.160 align:middle line:84%
>>ANNIE: That would be
two d's, wouldn't it?

00:37:21.160 --> 00:37:28.217 align:middle line:90%


00:37:28.217 --> 00:37:29.342 align:middle line:90%
>>CHRIS: I stand corrected.

00:37:29.342 --> 00:37:35.670 align:middle line:90%


00:37:35.670 --> 00:37:36.170 align:middle line:90%
[GASP]

00:37:36.170 --> 00:37:37.370 align:middle line:84%
>>CHRIS: Look what happens
when you don't say anything

00:37:37.370 --> 00:37:37.960 align:middle line:90%
for a month.

00:37:37.960 --> 00:37:42.040 align:middle line:90%


00:37:42.040 --> 00:37:43.936 align:middle line:90%
Cindy called.

00:37:43.936 --> 00:37:48.300 align:middle line:84%
She said everything's
waiting for you.

00:37:48.300 --> 00:37:51.440 align:middle line:84%
All the artists and
curators will meet with you

00:37:51.440 --> 00:37:54.480 align:middle line:90%
when you're better.

00:37:54.480 --> 00:38:02.600 align:middle line:84%
And I told her it was the
museum, one of those meetings

00:38:02.600 --> 00:38:04.717 align:middle line:84%
that kept you from
driving that day.

00:38:04.717 --> 00:38:08.060 align:middle line:90%


00:38:08.060 --> 00:38:11.682 align:middle line:84%
And if you went back, it
would mean you weren't sorry

00:38:11.682 --> 00:38:13.710 align:middle line:90%
and you weren't wrong.

00:38:13.710 --> 00:38:16.540 align:middle line:84%
And you would be
betraying your children.

00:38:16.540 --> 00:38:18.960 align:middle line:90%
And she said you were crazy.

00:38:18.960 --> 00:38:22.505 align:middle line:84%
And I said she was a soulless
bitch, and I hung up on her.

00:38:22.505 --> 00:38:23.755 align:middle line:90%
That didn't go over very well.

00:38:23.755 --> 00:38:29.880 align:middle line:90%


00:38:29.880 --> 00:38:34.430 align:middle line:84%
What's true in our minds is
true whether some people know it

00:38:34.430 --> 00:38:34.930 align:middle line:90%
or not.

00:38:34.930 --> 00:38:37.980 align:middle line:90%


00:38:37.980 --> 00:38:42.381 align:middle line:84%
That's when I realized
I'm part of the problem.

00:38:42.381 --> 00:38:49.820 align:middle line:84%
Not because I remind you, but
because I couldn't join you.

00:38:49.820 --> 00:38:51.280 align:middle line:90%
So I left you alone.

00:38:51.280 --> 00:38:59.746 align:middle line:90%


00:38:59.746 --> 00:39:01.240 align:middle line:90%
Don't give up, OK?

00:39:01.240 --> 00:39:06.220 align:middle line:90%


00:39:06.220 --> 00:39:07.216 align:middle line:90%
[SNIFFLING]

00:39:07.216 --> 00:39:14.188 align:middle line:90%


00:39:14.188 --> 00:39:17.176 align:middle line:90%
>>ANNIE: OK.

00:39:17.176 --> 00:39:19.168 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:39:19.168 --> 00:39:20.164 align:middle line:90%
[SOB]

00:39:20.164 --> 00:39:22.654 align:middle line:90%
>>CHRIS: It's OK.

00:39:22.654 --> 00:39:25.642 align:middle line:90%
[RIP]

00:39:25.642 --> 00:39:27.634 align:middle line:90%
[SOBBING]

00:39:27.634 --> 00:39:38.290 align:middle line:90%


00:39:38.290 --> 00:39:43.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So in this clip, he
went back into the dream state

00:39:43.550 --> 00:39:45.207 align:middle line:90%
to communicate with her?

00:39:45.207 --> 00:39:46.290 align:middle line:90%
Is that what he was doing?

00:39:46.290 --> 00:39:49.320 align:middle line:90%


00:39:49.320 --> 00:39:51.170 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: He went
into his own story.

00:39:51.170 --> 00:39:53.380 align:middle line:90%
You're absolutely right.

00:39:53.380 --> 00:39:55.950 align:middle line:90%
She had lost her children.

00:39:55.950 --> 00:39:57.990 align:middle line:90%
They'd both lost their children.

00:39:57.990 --> 00:40:05.060 align:middle line:84%
And she had such grief,
and he walled himself off

00:40:05.060 --> 00:40:07.110 align:middle line:84%
and went into denial
because he had

00:40:07.110 --> 00:40:09.350 align:middle line:84%
a story that he
needed to be strong.

00:40:09.350 --> 00:40:11.780 align:middle line:84%
And so she had nobody
to share that grief.

00:40:11.780 --> 00:40:13.360 align:middle line:84%
She had this power
in the telling,

00:40:13.360 --> 00:40:16.660 align:middle line:90%
and she was even more alienated.

00:40:16.660 --> 00:40:18.820 align:middle line:84%
She had her grief, and
she had the loneliness

00:40:18.820 --> 00:40:21.370 align:middle line:84%
of not being able to communicate
with him and share it.

00:40:21.370 --> 00:40:25.500 align:middle line:84%
And so she ended up having
to go to this asylum.

00:40:25.500 --> 00:40:28.507 align:middle line:84%
She had a nervous breakdown,
and he comes and visits her

00:40:28.507 --> 00:40:29.090 align:middle line:90%
at this point.

00:40:29.090 --> 00:40:30.750 align:middle line:90%
And he has this ticket.

00:40:30.750 --> 00:40:35.310 align:middle line:84%
And he says this
is a decision day.

00:40:35.310 --> 00:40:38.820 align:middle line:84%
This is a one-way ticket
decision about divorce.

00:40:38.820 --> 00:40:40.000 align:middle line:90%
So it says it's a d day.

00:40:40.000 --> 00:40:41.930 align:middle line:84%
She says well, that
would be double d day.

00:40:41.930 --> 00:40:44.760 align:middle line:84%
And now they're
having a conversation

00:40:44.760 --> 00:40:47.670 align:middle line:90%
about what really went on.

00:40:47.670 --> 00:40:51.250 align:middle line:84%
And he's realizing he left her
to do all the heavy lifting

00:40:51.250 --> 00:40:54.470 align:middle line:84%
around the emotions and that
he was protecting himself

00:40:54.470 --> 00:40:55.810 align:middle line:90%
not feeling anything.

00:40:55.810 --> 00:41:01.690 align:middle line:84%
So, to me, the beauty of this
is that when we're inside

00:41:01.690 --> 00:41:04.980 align:middle line:84%
our bubble, our stories,
the way we hold life,

00:41:04.980 --> 00:41:08.540 align:middle line:84%
we're so identified with it,
it's very difficult to change.

00:41:08.540 --> 00:41:09.550 align:middle line:90%
It's a fish in water.

00:41:09.550 --> 00:41:12.410 align:middle line:84%
But when that fish flings
itself up on the river bank,

00:41:12.410 --> 00:41:14.416 align:middle line:90%
it can then look back and say--

00:41:14.416 --> 00:41:15.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's water.

00:41:15.290 --> 00:41:16.860 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: --I came out of water.

00:41:16.860 --> 00:41:19.020 align:middle line:84%
So that's what is
happening here.

00:41:19.020 --> 00:41:20.630 align:middle line:90%
He gives it a name.

00:41:20.630 --> 00:41:22.302 align:middle line:90%
They call it double d.

00:41:22.302 --> 00:41:27.325 align:middle line:84%
And now they can begin
to relate to that story

00:41:27.325 --> 00:41:29.030 align:middle line:84%
rather than be
identified with it.

00:41:29.030 --> 00:41:33.020 align:middle line:84%
And when we do that, the
door to freedom swings open.

00:41:33.020 --> 00:41:35.610 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do we do
that in our own lives?

00:41:35.610 --> 00:41:41.650 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Well, how many times--
I'll speak personally--

00:41:41.650 --> 00:41:45.630 align:middle line:84%
things that I hold,
somebody disappointed me,

00:41:45.630 --> 00:41:50.360 align:middle line:84%
or I have a great thing
that I'm going on right now.

00:41:50.360 --> 00:41:54.250 align:middle line:84%
I have a number of work
relationships mostly

00:41:54.250 --> 00:41:57.180 align:middle line:84%
that have certain
accountabilities to me.

00:41:57.180 --> 00:42:04.900 align:middle line:84%
And about five of them
are out of integrity

00:42:04.900 --> 00:42:06.520 align:middle line:90%
around their accountability.

00:42:06.520 --> 00:42:11.667 align:middle line:84%
So now there is only one common
denominator in these five.

00:42:11.667 --> 00:42:12.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That would be you.

00:42:12.750 --> 00:42:14.291 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: So it'd be
really easy for me

00:42:14.291 --> 00:42:18.590 align:middle line:84%
to get very caught up in
the righteous indignation

00:42:18.590 --> 00:42:20.250 align:middle line:90%
or in the wagging finger.

00:42:20.250 --> 00:42:23.000 align:middle line:84%
But the reality is this
is five of these things,

00:42:23.000 --> 00:42:25.070 align:middle line:84%
and they're all
accountable to me.

00:42:25.070 --> 00:42:31.220 align:middle line:84%
So this is a mirror about
how I hold accountability

00:42:31.220 --> 00:42:32.930 align:middle line:90%
and what my expectations are.

00:42:32.930 --> 00:42:37.020 align:middle line:84%
So when I can see
that, I am calling it

00:42:37.020 --> 00:42:39.016 align:middle line:90%
my accountability story.

00:42:39.016 --> 00:42:40.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's interesting.

00:42:40.140 --> 00:42:40.640 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:42:40.640 --> 00:42:43.640 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Before I can really
have an effective communication

00:42:43.640 --> 00:42:48.350 align:middle line:84%
with these people, I'm
naming it I have a story,

00:42:48.350 --> 00:42:50.840 align:middle line:84%
and it should be like this,
and it should be like this,

00:42:50.840 --> 00:42:51.965 align:middle line:90%
and it should be like this.

00:42:51.965 --> 00:42:53.300 align:middle line:90%
And oh poor me.

00:42:53.300 --> 00:42:56.120 align:middle line:84%
So I'm calling that all
my accountability story,

00:42:56.120 --> 00:42:59.140 align:middle line:90%
and now I'm examining it.

00:42:59.140 --> 00:43:01.620 align:middle line:84%
And so because I'm
not inside of it,

00:43:01.620 --> 00:43:05.800 align:middle line:84%
I'm not just doing my knee jerk
habituated brittle responses.

00:43:05.800 --> 00:43:06.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:43:06.650 --> 00:43:10.150 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: But I can begin to
have a process with myself,

00:43:10.150 --> 00:43:14.700 align:middle line:84%
and free up some energy, and
look at what is going on here.

00:43:14.700 --> 00:43:17.780 align:middle line:84%
What might be some of
the elements in here

00:43:17.780 --> 00:43:25.160 align:middle line:84%
that would lead me to create
this repetitive pattern where

00:43:25.160 --> 00:43:27.095 align:middle line:84%
I have an opportunity
to be a victim?

00:43:27.095 --> 00:43:28.840 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's so interesting
because this whole interview

00:43:28.840 --> 00:43:30.380 align:middle line:84%
I've been talking about
your accountability

00:43:30.380 --> 00:43:31.340 align:middle line:90%
and authenticity.

00:43:31.340 --> 00:43:33.940 align:middle line:84%
And you don't even
know about that.

00:43:33.940 --> 00:43:36.600 align:middle line:84%
It just actually shows
that you are that way,

00:43:36.600 --> 00:43:39.440 align:middle line:84%
and that we do get stuck
inside of our story,

00:43:39.440 --> 00:43:43.170 align:middle line:84%
and that we form our own
stories around things.

00:43:43.170 --> 00:43:47.440 align:middle line:84%
Just as easily as we form
it, can we unform it?

00:43:47.440 --> 00:43:49.320 align:middle line:90%
Like what are you going to do?

00:43:49.320 --> 00:43:50.470 align:middle line:90%
You've looked at that.

00:43:50.470 --> 00:43:52.680 align:middle line:84%
You've stepped outside
of your story now.

00:43:52.680 --> 00:43:53.420 align:middle line:90%
What changes?

00:43:53.420 --> 00:43:55.820 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: I am making a
friend of uncertainty

00:43:55.820 --> 00:43:58.630 align:middle line:84%
because I would really love
to just have the answers.

00:43:58.630 --> 00:44:00.664 align:middle line:84%
And there's nothing
creative in that.

00:44:00.664 --> 00:44:01.705 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Have it complete.

00:44:01.705 --> 00:44:02.205 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: Yes.

00:44:02.205 --> 00:44:04.653 align:middle line:84%
Can it just be complete
because I'm uncomfortable?

00:44:04.653 --> 00:44:05.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:44:05.480 --> 00:44:12.540 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: So I am watching
my discomfort as much

00:44:12.540 --> 00:44:15.540 align:middle line:84%
as I can because it
is not my default

00:44:15.540 --> 00:44:18.990 align:middle line:84%
way of operating in
the world is to feel.

00:44:18.990 --> 00:44:23.990 align:middle line:84%
So I am feeling as much
as I can the discomfort,

00:44:23.990 --> 00:44:27.300 align:middle line:84%
I'm not running from it, and I'm
allowing what comes up in its

00:44:27.300 --> 00:44:32.920 align:middle line:84%
own cadence and its own timing
to come up before I go back

00:44:32.920 --> 00:44:41.500 align:middle line:84%
and instead of having the
conversation that I would have

00:44:41.500 --> 00:44:44.940 align:middle line:84%
had, which would have been
probably not pretty and not

00:44:44.940 --> 00:44:50.330 align:middle line:84%
helpful, I'm waiting
for--and I don't know what.

00:44:50.330 --> 00:44:52.310 align:middle line:90%
I don't have an answer here.

00:44:52.310 --> 00:44:55.870 align:middle line:84%
I don't have an answer, but I'm
waiting for something creative

00:44:55.870 --> 00:45:02.280 align:middle line:84%
to emerge in me that allows me
to be more responsible for what

00:45:02.280 --> 00:45:07.000 align:middle line:84%
is going on than I would
have been if I just went off

00:45:07.000 --> 00:45:11.839 align:middle line:84%
unprepared at the limit of
my potential to be prepared.

00:45:11.839 --> 00:45:13.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So this is you living--

00:45:13.130 --> 00:45:14.050 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: This is
new ground for me.

00:45:14.050 --> 00:45:15.010 align:middle line:90%
You can tell, I don't--

00:45:15.010 --> 00:45:15.926 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: This is great.

00:45:15.926 --> 00:45:18.140 align:middle line:84%
No, but this is how you
are experiencing it.

00:45:18.140 --> 00:45:20.190 align:middle line:90%
And this is being creative.

00:45:20.190 --> 00:45:22.050 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: This is being creative.

00:45:22.050 --> 00:45:25.380 align:middle line:90%
Creativity happens in the heart.

00:45:25.380 --> 00:45:27.830 align:middle line:84%
It happens in a space
behind the heart.

00:45:27.830 --> 00:45:30.880 align:middle line:84%
That is the portal through
which we experience

00:45:30.880 --> 00:45:33.350 align:middle line:90%
what is innovative and creative.

00:45:33.350 --> 00:45:38.540 align:middle line:84%
Then kicks in this
magnificent inner-engineer

00:45:38.540 --> 00:45:45.740 align:middle line:84%
strategic technician, the doer,
the integrated masculine energy

00:45:45.740 --> 00:45:49.080 align:middle line:84%
that fills the space and
creates form out of function.

00:45:49.080 --> 00:45:52.890 align:middle line:84%
That's beautiful, but when we
are estranged from this part,

00:45:52.890 --> 00:45:57.370 align:middle line:84%
it can go off and
sometimes be a mania.

00:45:57.370 --> 00:45:59.480 align:middle line:84%
You know, when you're
just doing, doing, doing,

00:45:59.480 --> 00:46:04.820 align:middle line:84%
and it's unrelated to
making the context bigger,

00:46:04.820 --> 00:46:08.030 align:middle line:84%
and making the context new,
and making the context fresh.

00:46:08.030 --> 00:46:10.570 align:middle line:84%
So what happens
between the doing

00:46:10.570 --> 00:46:15.010 align:middle line:84%
and the being state,
in between those

00:46:15.010 --> 00:46:16.835 align:middle line:84%
is birthed some
kind of revelation.

00:46:16.835 --> 00:46:18.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's
what, reinvention?

00:46:18.210 --> 00:46:19.045 align:middle line:90%
That's what--

00:46:19.045 --> 00:46:20.170 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: That's reinvention.

00:46:20.170 --> 00:46:21.100 align:middle line:90%
That's innovation.

00:46:21.100 --> 00:46:23.060 align:middle line:90%
That's where the juicy stuff is.

00:46:23.060 --> 00:46:24.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's where
creativity comes.

00:46:24.700 --> 00:46:29.180 align:middle line:84%
So, as I said earlier, you
choose scripts and stories

00:46:29.180 --> 00:46:31.610 align:middle line:84%
based on your emotions
and feelings around them.

00:46:31.610 --> 00:46:33.720 align:middle line:84%
There's another film
that you showed me,

00:46:33.720 --> 00:46:35.000 align:middle line:90%
which I think is wonderful.

00:46:35.000 --> 00:46:38.130 align:middle line:84%
It's called from
"Homeless to Harvard."

00:46:38.130 --> 00:46:42.180 align:middle line:84%
How did you come
across this story?

00:46:42.180 --> 00:46:43.600 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: This is
a while back now.

00:46:43.600 --> 00:46:46.410 align:middle line:90%
I was in my agent's office.

00:46:46.410 --> 00:46:50.650 align:middle line:84%
And he got up to do something
outside of the room.

00:46:50.650 --> 00:46:53.880 align:middle line:84%
And that would be my
cue to actually see

00:46:53.880 --> 00:46:56.320 align:middle line:84%
what might be
interesting in here.

00:46:56.320 --> 00:46:58.480 align:middle line:84%
And I found this
thing on the floor.

00:46:58.480 --> 00:47:05.454 align:middle line:84%
And it was an interview
between Liz Murray

00:47:05.454 --> 00:47:07.370 align:middle line:84%
and I think with Barbara
Walters, or something

00:47:07.370 --> 00:47:07.870 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:47:07.870 --> 00:47:10.092 align:middle line:84%
And I was fascinated by
it, "Homeless to Harvard."

00:47:10.092 --> 00:47:11.300 align:middle line:90%
I thought that's interesting.

00:47:11.300 --> 00:47:13.700 align:middle line:84%
And when he came back
in, I asked him about it.

00:47:13.700 --> 00:47:15.700 align:middle line:84%
And he told me it
was a true story

00:47:15.700 --> 00:47:20.970 align:middle line:84%
of Liz Murray, a young
girl whose parents were

00:47:20.970 --> 00:47:24.590 align:middle line:84%
both drug addicted and
had AIDS in the Bronx.

00:47:24.590 --> 00:47:26.560 align:middle line:84%
And the mother passed
away, and the young girl

00:47:26.560 --> 00:47:30.560 align:middle line:84%
ended up on the streets and
realized her only way out

00:47:30.560 --> 00:47:34.950 align:middle line:84%
was going to be to have a
zero tolerance for self-pity

00:47:34.950 --> 00:47:36.300 align:middle line:90%
and to apply herself.

00:47:36.300 --> 00:47:38.185 align:middle line:90%
And she--

00:47:38.185 --> 00:47:39.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A true story?

00:47:39.060 --> 00:47:39.934 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: --true story.

00:47:39.934 --> 00:47:42.780 align:middle line:84%
She went through four years
of college and two years

00:47:42.780 --> 00:47:44.860 align:middle line:84%
living on the subway and
eating out of dumpsters.

00:47:44.860 --> 00:47:48.170 align:middle line:84%
And she earned a
scholarship to Harvard.

00:47:48.170 --> 00:47:52.990 align:middle line:84%
And she is a hero
of mine, a shero.

00:47:52.990 --> 00:47:53.907 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A shero?

00:47:53.907 --> 00:47:55.490 align:middle line:84%
We actually have a
clip of this, which

00:47:55.490 --> 00:47:59.200 align:middle line:84%
is a wonderful-- I'm amazed
that this is a true story,

00:47:59.200 --> 00:48:00.360 align:middle line:90%
and she did this.

00:48:00.360 --> 00:48:01.671 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look at this.

00:48:01.671 --> 00:48:03.420 align:middle line:84%
>>MALE SPEAKER: She
did it while homeless.

00:48:03.420 --> 00:48:05.650 align:middle line:84%
Her mother dead, her
father a drug addict,

00:48:05.650 --> 00:48:07.820 align:middle line:84%
living in shelters,
and any way I

00:48:07.820 --> 00:48:11.010 align:middle line:84%
describe this can't do justice
to her accomplishments,

00:48:11.010 --> 00:48:13.980 align:middle line:84%
so I'll just introduce to
you our sixth New York Times

00:48:13.980 --> 00:48:16.674 align:middle line:90%
scholarship winner, Liz Murray.

00:48:16.674 --> 00:48:18.156 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:48:18.156 --> 00:48:26.560 align:middle line:90%


00:48:26.560 --> 00:48:29.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LIZ: Everything's changed.

00:48:29.700 --> 00:48:32.320 align:middle line:90%
My life will never be the same.

00:48:32.320 --> 00:48:36.250 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know what else
to say except for thank you.

00:48:36.250 --> 00:48:37.250 align:middle line:90%
Thank you very much.

00:48:37.250 --> 00:48:39.750 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:48:39.750 --> 00:48:41.250 align:middle line:90%
>>MALE SPEAKER: Liz?

00:48:41.250 --> 00:48:42.710 align:middle line:90%
Liz?

00:48:42.710 --> 00:48:43.980 align:middle line:90%
How'd you do this?

00:48:43.980 --> 00:48:46.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LIZ: How could I not do it?

00:48:46.600 --> 00:48:48.920 align:middle line:84%
My parents showed me
what the alternative was.

00:48:48.920 --> 00:48:51.740 align:middle line:84%
>>MALE SPEAKER: Didn't you
ever feel sorry for yourself?

00:48:51.740 --> 00:48:52.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LIZ: Sorry?

00:48:52.300 --> 00:48:53.800 align:middle line:84%
>>MALE SPEAKER:
Sleeping in subways,

00:48:53.800 --> 00:48:57.270 align:middle line:90%
eating out of dumpsters?

00:48:57.270 --> 00:49:00.760 align:middle line:84%
>>LIZ: That had always,
uh, been my life.

00:49:00.760 --> 00:49:04.190 align:middle line:84%
And I really-- I
feel that I got lucky

00:49:04.190 --> 00:49:09.240 align:middle line:84%
because any sense of security
was pulled out from under me.

00:49:09.240 --> 00:49:11.110 align:middle line:90%
So I was forced to look forward.

00:49:11.110 --> 00:49:11.920 align:middle line:90%
I had to.

00:49:11.920 --> 00:49:15.020 align:middle line:90%
There was no going back.

00:49:15.020 --> 00:49:19.220 align:middle line:84%
And I reached a point where
I just thought, all right.

00:49:19.220 --> 00:49:22.090 align:middle line:84%
I'm gonna work as
hard as I possibly can

00:49:22.090 --> 00:49:25.330 align:middle line:90%
and see what happens.

00:49:25.330 --> 00:49:27.680 align:middle line:90%
And now I'm going to college.

00:49:27.680 --> 00:49:31.056 align:middle line:84%
And, uh, and the New York
Times is going to pay.

00:49:31.056 --> 00:49:32.014 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER AND APPLAUSE]

00:49:32.014 --> 00:49:34.882 align:middle line:90%


00:49:34.882 --> 00:49:39.620 align:middle line:84%
>>MALE SPEAKER: So you
were lucky, but is there

00:49:39.620 --> 00:49:44.275 align:middle line:84%
anything you'd change
if you were able?

00:49:44.275 --> 00:49:44.775 align:middle line:90%
>>LIZ: Yeah.

00:49:44.775 --> 00:49:48.260 align:middle line:90%


00:49:48.260 --> 00:49:59.110 align:middle line:84%
I'd give it back, all of it,
if I could have my family back.

00:49:59.110 --> 00:50:02.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's amazing
how a minute long clip

00:50:02.200 --> 00:50:04.550 align:middle line:90%
could make me cry.

00:50:04.550 --> 00:50:07.400 align:middle line:90%
It is such a powerful story.

00:50:07.400 --> 00:50:11.440 align:middle line:84%
And she stuck with
what she believed in

00:50:11.440 --> 00:50:14.360 align:middle line:84%
even though she had no
reference in her life.

00:50:14.360 --> 00:50:18.180 align:middle line:84%
She was dealt a bad deck, and
she made the best out of it

00:50:18.180 --> 00:50:21.220 align:middle line:84%
when she had to treat
her mother as her baby.

00:50:21.220 --> 00:50:23.720 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that really
broke the mold.

00:50:23.720 --> 00:50:28.020 align:middle line:84%
How do you teach people to
stick with what you believe in,

00:50:28.020 --> 00:50:31.240 align:middle line:84%
to not go after the
shiny, bright whatever,

00:50:31.240 --> 00:50:33.679 align:middle line:84%
and to stay true to
what you believe in?

00:50:33.679 --> 00:50:36.220 align:middle line:84%
In the projects you choose, and
the creativity that you have,

00:50:36.220 --> 00:50:38.970 align:middle line:84%
and the relationships that
you have, how do you do that?

00:50:38.970 --> 00:50:41.240 align:middle line:90%
You've done that.

00:50:41.240 --> 00:50:43.370 align:middle line:90%
>>BAIN: It's an ongoing process.

00:50:43.370 --> 00:50:47.440 align:middle line:90%
And it has to do with values.

00:50:47.440 --> 00:50:51.037 align:middle line:84%
I map my values, and I
encourage other people

00:50:51.037 --> 00:50:51.870 align:middle line:90%
to map their values.

00:50:51.870 --> 00:50:53.203 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And what does that mean?

00:50:53.203 --> 00:50:57.350 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: --to be clear on what
I value, and what you value,

00:50:57.350 --> 00:51:00.050 align:middle line:84%
we have certain kinds
of areas in our life.

00:51:00.050 --> 00:51:03.970 align:middle line:84%
There is my career life,
and my home and family life,

00:51:03.970 --> 00:51:06.530 align:middle line:84%
and my spiritual life,
and my hobby life,

00:51:06.530 --> 00:51:10.590 align:middle line:84%
and my recreational life,
my life around health.

00:51:10.590 --> 00:51:13.510 align:middle line:90%
And so it's like a wheel.

00:51:13.510 --> 00:51:18.440 align:middle line:84%
And I grade them,
and I make sure

00:51:18.440 --> 00:51:21.700 align:middle line:84%
that I am feeding
attention into,

00:51:21.700 --> 00:51:24.650 align:middle line:84%
so that they don't go out of
balance so that I don't become

00:51:24.650 --> 00:51:28.130 align:middle line:84%
a workaholic, or so that I
don't become somebody who's

00:51:28.130 --> 00:51:32.760 align:middle line:84%
escaping life through
eating or whatever it is.

00:51:32.760 --> 00:51:36.530 align:middle line:84%
I do my best to
keep them modulated.

00:51:36.530 --> 00:51:39.910 align:middle line:84%
And because these
things are my values,

00:51:39.910 --> 00:51:43.230 align:middle line:84%
and when I score
them on a 1 to 10,

00:51:43.230 --> 00:51:47.460 align:middle line:84%
I can see where I
give more attention

00:51:47.460 --> 00:51:48.900 align:middle line:90%
and where I give less attention.

00:51:48.900 --> 00:51:50.820 align:middle line:90%
And I try to balance them out.

00:51:50.820 --> 00:51:53.490 align:middle line:90%


00:51:53.490 --> 00:51:57.970 align:middle line:84%
When I know my values, I have
an opportunity to express

00:51:57.970 --> 00:52:03.440 align:middle line:84%
character because one cannot
have character without having

00:52:03.440 --> 00:52:05.870 align:middle line:90%
values.

00:52:05.870 --> 00:52:10.354 align:middle line:84%
Character to me is the degree
to which I live by my values.

00:52:10.354 --> 00:52:12.020 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's the same
thing, in essence?

00:52:12.020 --> 00:52:14.394 align:middle line:84%
>>BAIN: Well, if I'm living
in accordance with my values,

00:52:14.394 --> 00:52:15.830 align:middle line:90%
I have character.

00:52:15.830 --> 00:52:17.970 align:middle line:84%
If I don't know
what my values are,

00:52:17.970 --> 00:52:21.840 align:middle line:84%
then my character is
all over the place.

00:52:21.840 --> 00:52:27.140 align:middle line:84%
So when I have values, and my
values are always deepening,

00:52:27.140 --> 00:52:31.170 align:middle line:84%
I will never ever achieve
perfect character.

00:52:31.170 --> 00:52:34.980 align:middle line:90%
But it's like the guiding star.

00:52:34.980 --> 00:52:38.220 align:middle line:84%
It's a mission that is
bigger than this life,

00:52:38.220 --> 00:52:39.810 align:middle line:90%
and it informs my choices.

00:52:39.810 --> 00:52:44.240 align:middle line:84%
So now it's very clear that
if I have an opportunity

00:52:44.240 --> 00:52:51.940 align:middle line:84%
to take on a project or
to make a choice that

00:52:51.940 --> 00:52:56.600 align:middle line:84%
is inconsistent with what my
values are, I absolutely know.

00:52:56.600 --> 00:52:59.460 align:middle line:90%
And I can't hide from myself.

00:52:59.460 --> 00:53:01.310 align:middle line:84%
You become very
honest with yourself.

00:53:01.310 --> 00:53:07.470 align:middle line:84%
But one has to know what are
the lines that I will not

00:53:07.470 --> 00:53:10.790 align:middle line:84%
cross in the various areas
of my life in order for me

00:53:10.790 --> 00:53:12.800 align:middle line:84%
to know whether
I'm crossing them.

00:53:12.800 --> 00:53:14.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: In what you're
doing now and how

00:53:14.700 --> 00:53:17.160 align:middle line:84%
this has evolved into
your life now-- of course,

00:53:17.160 --> 00:53:18.350 align:middle line:90%
media is changing.

00:53:18.350 --> 00:53:21.620 align:middle line:84%
We have Gaiam TV, which
is online media, which

00:53:21.620 --> 00:53:24.940 align:middle line:84%
